{"type":"message","id":"90f61b30","parentId":"25ef30a8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:55:42.074Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hpmape7ico5y_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 194521\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/tic_classifier.py (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful next action.\r\n\r\nFrom the context:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture cross-analysis) are complete\r\n- Gap-decay synthesis is done\r\n- LLM-Augmented pulse system is working\r\n- A major insight has emerged: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - compression and causal discovery are the SAME problem\r\n- Next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n\r\nThe pending action is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete, specific action that advances the main goal. I should create a Python script or PowerShell wrapper that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Implements the TIC classifier to identify invariants vs variants\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Measures accuracy against the success criteria\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script for the TIC experiment since it's more suitable for text processing and machine learning tasks.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight provides a concrete path forward: if causal structure IS invariant structure, we can test this by building a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on existing pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python script that implements the TIC experiment to classify pulse content as invariant (stable across pulses) vs variant (changing), then measure prediction accuracy. This directly tests the core hypothesis that compression discovers causation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\nSuccess criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_content(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract text content from pulse log, excluding headers.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    # Remove frontmatter if present\r\n    if content.startswith('---'):\r\n        parts = content.split('---', 2)\r\n        if len(parts) >= 3:\r\n            content = parts[2]\r\n    return content.strip()\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Simple word tokenization.\"\"\"\r\n    return re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*\\b', text.lower())\r\n\r\ndef extract_ngrams(text, n=3):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract n-grams as features.\"\"\"\r\n    tokens = tokenize(text)\r\n    return ['_'.join(tokens[i:i+n]) for i in range(len(tokens)-n+1)]\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariant_score(current, previous, threshold=0.3):\r\n    \"\"\"Score how invariant current is relative to previous.\r\n    Returns 1.0 if highly invariant (high overlap), 0.0 if highly variant.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if not previous:\r\n        return 0.5  # Unknown baseline\r\n    \r\n    curr_ngrams = set(extract_ngrams(current, n=3))\r\n    prev_ngrams = set(extract_ngrams(previous, n=3))\r\n    \r\n    if not curr_ngrams or not prev_ngrams:\r\n        return 0.5\r\n    \r\n    overlap = len(curr_ngrams & prev_ngrams)\r\n    union = len(curr_ngrams | prev_ngrams)\r\n    \r\n    jaccard = overlap / union if union > 0 else 0\r\n    \r\n    # Convert to invariant score (high overlap = high invariance)\r\n    return jaccard\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(variant_score, threshold=0.35):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify based on score threshold.\"\"\"\r\n    return \"INVARIANT\" if variant_score >= threshold else \"VARIANT\"\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(current_content, invariant_ngrams):\r\n    \"\"\"Simple prediction: if n-gram appears in invariants, expect to persist.\"\"\"\r\n    current_ngrams = set(extract_ngrams(current_content, n=3))\r\n    predicted_persistent = current_ngrams & invariant_ngrams\r\n    return predicted_persistent\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    # Collect pulse logs sorted by timestamp\r\n    pulse_files = []\r\n    for f in LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"):\r\n        match = PULSE_PATTERN.match(f.name)\r\n        if match:\r\n            pulse_files.append((match.group(1), f))\r\n    pulse_files.sort(key=lambda x: x[0])\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 3:\r\n        print(f\"Need at least 3 pulse logs, found {len(pulse_files)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Extract content\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for ts, fp in pulse_files:\r\n        content = extract_pulse_content(fp)\r\n        pulses.append((ts, content))\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"=== TIC Experiment: {len(pulses)} pulses analyzed ===\\n\")\r\n    \r\n    # Build invariant n-gram set from first 50% of pulses\r\n    split_idx = len(pulses) // 2\r\n    training_pulses = pulses[:split_idx]\r\n    test_pulses = pulses[split_idx:]\r\n    \r\n    invariant_ngrams = set()\r\n    for _, content in training_pulses:\r\n        invariant_ngrams.update(extract_ngrams(content, n=3))\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"Training: {len(training_pulses)} pulses, {len(invariant_ngrams)} invariant n-grams\\n\")\r\n    \r\n    # Classification experiment\r\n    classifications = []\r\n    for i in range(1,\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 19:45:51\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774310142073}}
