{"type":"message","id":"91f1905b","parentId":"7c5b6161","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:55:47.057Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2pqn2jpmj9x3_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 195521\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine ONE concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- Key insight: \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - Problem 1 and Problem 2 are the same\r\n- NEXT ACTION is the TIC Experiment:\r\n  - Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n  - Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n  - Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n  - Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to actually implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier. I need to:\r\n\r\n1. First, understand what the pulse logs look like\r\n2. Design the TIC classifier\r\n3. Implement it\r\n\r\nLet me think about what the TIC classifier should do:\r\n- It needs to read through the pulse log files\r\n- Classify content as \"invariant\" (stable across pulses) or \"variant\" (changing)\r\n- Use this to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nFor a concrete, file-editing action, I should:\r\n1. Create the TIC classifier script (PowerShell or Python)\r\n2. Define the significance scoring for pulse content\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- [ ] Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n- [ ] Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- [ ] Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe most impactful single action would be to define the significance scoring system, since that's foundational for the TIC experiment. Or I could start implementing the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete implementation plan. I'll create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariants (content that repeats across sessions)\r\n\r\n\r\n3. Identifies variants (content that changes)\r\n4. Uses this to make predictions\r\n\r\nI'll focus on crafting a script that systematically processes pulse log data, extracting recurring and changing patterns to enable meaningful classification and prediction.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step, but I need to establish the significance scoring first to enable invariant/variant classification. This scoring system is foundational for both the classifier and the compression ratio measurement.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the significance scoring module that defines how pulse content is evaluated for invariance - this will be the core algorithm for TIC classification across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) - Significance Scoring\r\n# Phase: Active Experiment | Updated: 2026-03-23\r\n\r\n## Significance Scoring Algorithm\r\n\r\n### Core Principle\r\nContent is **significant** if it persists OR if its absence is informative.\r\n\r\n### Scoring Function: σ(content, pulse_history)\r\n```\r\nσ = λ × persistence_rate + (1-λ) × information_gain\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhere:\r\n- `λ` = decay/gap sensitivity parameter (start: 0.7)\r\n- `persistence_rate` = proportion of recent pulses containing this content\r\n- `information_gain` = reduction in uncertainty given this content\r\n\r\n### Classification Thresholds\r\n- **INVARIANT**: σ ≥ 0.65 (stable across sessions)\r\n- **VARIANT**: σ < 0.65 (session-dependent)\r\n- **SIGNIFICANT**: σ ≥ 0.50 (warrants inclusion in compressed state)\r\n\r\n### Implementation\r\n```powershell\r\nfunction Get-SignificanceScore {\r\n    param(\r\n        [string]$Content,\r\n        [array]$PulseHistory,\r\n        [float]$Lambda = 0.7\r\n    )\r\n    \r\n    $recentPulses = $PulseHistory | Select-Object -Last(10)\r\n    $persistenceRate = ($recentPulses | Where-Object { $_.Content -match $Content }).Count / $recentPulses.Count\r\n    \r\n    # Simplified: persistence IS the significance for now\r\n    return $Lambda * $persistenceRate + (1 - $Lambda) * $persistenceRate\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Classify-Content {\r\n    param(\r\n        [string]$Content,\r\n        [array]$PulseHistory,\r\n        [float]$Lambda = 0.7\r\n    )\r\n    \r\n    $score = Get-SignificanceScore -Content $Content -PulseHistory $PulseHistory -Lambda $Lambda\r\n    \r\n    if ($score -ge 0.65) { return \"INVARIANT\" }\r\n    elseif ($score -ge 0.50) { return \"SIGNIFICANT\" }\r\n    else { return \"VARIANT\" }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Success Criteria\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n### Files\r\n- `src/tic/classifier.ps1` - Main classifier\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` - Input data\r\n- `research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md` - Results\r\nfile: research/TIC-SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 19:55:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774310147055}}
