{"type":"message","id":"cd9613a1","parentId":"23f8e8a4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:55:49.917Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bszgqxoarvok_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"research/TIC-SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) - Significance Scoring\n# Phase: Active Experiment | Updated: 2026-03-23\n\n## Significance Scoring Algorithm\n\n### Core Principle\nContent is **significant** if it persists OR if its absence is informative.\n\n### Scoring Function: σ(content, pulse_history)\n\n\nWhere:\n- `λ` = decay/gap sensitivity parameter (start: 0.7)\n- `persistence_rate` = proportion of recent pulses containing this content\n- `information_gain` = reduction in uncertainty given this content\n\n### Classification Thresholds\n- **INVARIANT**: σ ≥ 0.65 (stable across sessions)\n- **VARIANT**: σ < 0.65 (session-dependent)\n- **SIGNIFICANT**: σ ≥ 0.50 (warrants inclusion in compressed state)\n\n### Implementation\n\n\n### Success Criteria\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction accuracy\n\n### Files\n- `src/tic/classifier.ps1` - Main classifier\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` - Input data\n- `research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md` - Results\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774310149914}}
